@dev
 | The Trust Anchor Extra Data [Unique] reference contract
 | This contract is an example of the type of parameters most useful in a Regulatory/Onboarding/Verification context. A very malleable construction of variables is used, with:
 | a) a mapping of hashes (for lookups on various databases) with a string name for human readability.
 | b) a mapping of ip endpoints (for the transfer of sensitive documents) with a string name for human readability.
 | c) a mapping of 256-bit numeric identifiers (for various indexing purposes) with a string name for human readability.
 | d) a string for public metadata.
@dev Event for creating an End Point
@dev Event for updating an End Point
@dev Event for Data Retrieval Endpoint is Enabled for a specific Endpoint name.
@dev Event for creating a Hash Mapping
@dev Event for updating a Hash Mapping
@dev Event for creating a Numeric Identifier
@dev Event for updating a Numeric Identifier
@dev Event for creating a Key-Value Pair (String to String relationship)
@dev Event for updating a Key-Value Pair (String to String relationship)
@dev Event for setting Public Metadata
@dev Mapping for a Trust Anchor to its unique extraData parameters.
@dev The owner of this contract.
@dev The Trust Anchor Manager address that this contract is bound to.
@dev Initializes this contract with the owner set to the calling public address.

@dev Gets the Trust Anchor Manager associated to this contract.
 @return result trust anchor manager address
